    {
      "id": "PopularPost283714",
      "post_content": "Armillary Sphere is a card that finds its way into my mono-red EDH decks, but little else. This color, in particular, is lacking in two key areas: mana development and card draw. This card contributes a little to both, in a rather indirect way.  \n  \nRed decks have access to pretty much all the same mana rocks other colors do, but little beyond that baseline to keep pace with other colors' development. While the Sphere doesn't actually accelerate mana, it helps hit land drops. Red needs that extra help when it's not searching up lands in the early game from [Brainstorm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brainstorm) and [Cultivate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cultivate)-type effects. With that dearth of non-land mana sources, red decks really need to hit as many land drops as they can up until the latest stages of the game, in hope to keep up.  \n  \nRed is lacking in conventional draw, but it's getting ever better at cycling away unwanted cards (via [WInds of Change](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=WInds of Change), [Incendiary Command](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Incendiary Command), [Faith](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Faith)... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "voyager1",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost283714\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl05_post\">Armillary Sphere is a card that finds its way into my mono-red EDH decks, but little else. This color, in particular, is lacking in two key areas: mana development and card draw. This card contributes a little to both, in a rather indirect way.<br/><br/>Red decks have access to pretty much all the same mana rocks other colors do, but little beyond that baseline to keep pace with other colors' development. While the Sphere doesn't actually accelerate mana, it helps hit land drops. Red needs that extra help when it's not searching up lands in the early game from <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Brainstorm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brainstorm\">Brainstorm</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Cultivate\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cultivate\">Cultivate</a>-type effects. With that dearth of non-land mana sources, red decks really need to hit as many land drops as they can up until the latest stages of the game, in hope to keep up.<br/><br/>Red is lacking in conventional draw, but it's getting ever better at cycling away unwanted cards (via <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"WInds of Change\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=WInds of Change\">WInds of Change</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Incendiary Command\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Incendiary Command\">Incendiary Command</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Faith\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Faith\">Faith</a>... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 283714)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl05_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizard